**Detailed Project Note: Smart Counter**<mccoremem id="01KR0SAN069XDXFEQ3RBCB9RYC" />\
\
**Overview**\
Smart Counter is a high-performance computer vision application designed to automate object detection and counting tasks. By utilizing the state-of-the-art **YOLOv8** (You Only Look Once) architecture, the project provides real-time insights into visual data, whether from static uploads or live video streams.\
\
**Core Features**\
- **Dual Operating Modes**:\
  - **Web Dashboard**: An interactive Gradio interface for processing uploaded images.\
  - **Live Stream**: A local OpenCV-based script for real-time counting via webcam.\
- **Multi-Class Detection**: Automatically identifies and counts multiple object categories simultaneously (e.g., people, cars, chairs, etc.).\
- **Visual Feedback**: Provides annotated visual outputs with bounding boxes and dynamic labels.\
- **Instant Summaries**: Generates a clean text breakdown of all detected objects and their respective counts.\
\
**Technical Stack**\
- **Model**: [yolov8n.pt](file:///Users/mohammedthahers/Desktop/Projects/smart_counter/yolov8n.pt) (Nano version) \'97 optimized for high speed and low latency.\
- **Frameworks**:\
  - **Ultralytics**: Simplifies the implementation of the YOLOv8 model.\
  - **Gradio**: Handles the UI/UX for the web application.\
  - **OpenCV**: Manages hardware integration (webcam) and image manipulation.\
- **Language**: Python 3.x.\
\
**Component Breakdown**\
- [app.py](file:///Users/mohammedthahers/Desktop/Projects/smart_counter/app.py): Implements the `count_objects` logic and launches the Gradio server. It converts PIL images to NumPy arrays for processing and back to PIL for display.\
- [counter.py](file:///Users/mohammedthahers/Desktop/Projects/smart_counter/counter.py): A standalone script for low-latency live detection. It uses a `while` loop to capture frames and `cv2.putText` to overlay real-time stats.\
- [test.py](file:///Users/mohammedthahers/Desktop/Projects/smart_counter/test.py): A utility script used to verify model loading and basic detection functionality.\
\
**Setup and Execution**\
1. **Install Dependencies**:\
   ```bash\
   pip install -r requirements.txt\
   ```\
2. **Launch Web App**:\
   ```bash\
   python app.py\
   ```\
3. **Run Real-time Counter**:\
   ```bash\
   python counter.py\
   ```\
\
**Use Cases**\
- **Retail**: Monitoring customer footfall or shelf inventory.\
- **Traffic Management**: Counting vehicles in intersections.\
- **Industrial**: Quality control and part counting on assembly lines.\
- **Accessibility**: Assisting visually impaired users by identifying surrounding objects.\
